title._content: After Her Car Failed the Emissions Test at an Auto Emission Inspection Station in Downtown Cincinnati, Ohio...09/1975

description._content: Original Caption: After Her Car Failed the Emissions Test at an Auto Emission Inspection Station in Downtown Cincinnati, Ohio, This Young Woman Heads for a Service Station and Engine Adjustment. All Light Duty Spark Ignition Powered Motor Vehicles Must Pass Carbon Monoxide and Hydrocarbon Emissions Tests Annually as Well as a Safety Check That Has Been in Effect Since 1940. All Other Type Vehicles Registered in the City Must Undergo Only the Safety Check. 09/1975 U.S. National Archives’ Local Identifier: 412-DA-15473 Photographer: Eiler, Lyntha Scott, 1946- Subjects: Cincinnati (Hamilton county, Ohio, United States) inhabited place Environmental Protection Agency Project DOCUMERICA Persistent URL: arcweb.archives.gov/arc/action/ExternalIdSearch?id=557923 Repository: Still Picture Records Section, Special Media Archives Services Division (NWCS-S), National Archives at College Park, 8601 Adelphi Road, College Park, MD, 20740-6001.
